/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-003-bounded-observable-table.md:83:| `tube coherence / persistence` | secondary comparator | [INFERRED] not clearly scale-invariant by itself; it inherits any scale-credibility only from the fixed `r^{-2}` threshold and dyadic scale package | [INFERRED] depends on connectedness/coherence of intense components inside the Eulerian thresholded set across the parabolic window | [INFERRED] mainly filament/tube primary scenario; [INFERRED] useful only as a misfit detector on the sheet/pancake comparator | [INFERRED] could only matter by suppressing exterior/inter-scale stretching or localization-evolution cost; tube existence alone does not point to a smaller term | [VERIFIED/INFERRED] one-time tube-shaped concentration is Tao-robust; only persistence across scales/time is plausibly destroyed by averaging | [VERIFIED/INFERRED] very prone to descriptive slippage: if the table cannot say what full-stretching term becomes smaller, tube language is dead even if coherent structures look vivid |
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-003-bounded-observable-table.md:85:| `Beltrami deficit + concentration` | fragility screen only | [INFERRED] normalization is fragile because concentration strength depends explicitly on the thresholded intense set; any advantage is hostage to threshold choice | [INFERRED] depends on alignment plus the Eulerian thresholded concentration profile in `E_r(t)` | [INFERRED] mostly filament/tube primary scenario, but only as a diagnostic hybrid | [INFERRED] hoped leverage would be a more favorable core-versus-exterior split, but the local record contains no full-stretching bridge under the fixed package | [INFERRED] only a dynamic coupling between concentrated aligned cores and a smaller full-stretching term would beat Tao-style robustness | [INFERRED] easiest place for hidden normalization: if the hybrid looks good only because the threshold isolates unusually aligned cores, the route is manufactured by localization |
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-003-bounded-observable-table.md:115:  - `Beltrami deficit + concentration`
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-003-bounded-observable-table.md:152:    `Beltrami deficit + concentration`,
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The problem is that the chain still overestimates what "exact packet structure" is likely to buy. Exact helical triad bookkeeping is real, but real is not the same as coercive. Waleffe-style interaction geometry, same-helicity suppression, and decimated-sector advantages have been around for a long time. The hard issue is not whether one can write a packet-complete ledger. The hard issue is whether any sign or exclusion effect survives full mixed-helicity completion, shell summation, localization, pressure restoration, and insertion into an LEI/CKN-facing endpoint. That is exactly where these ideas usually die.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The candidate "bad transfer patterns" are not interchangeable. Comparable-scale stretching production, shell-bridging concentration feed, and similar targets sit at different levels of the problem. One might be natural in helical triad language while another is only natural on an LEI/CKN ledger. Letting the route pick whichever is most packet-friendly invites target shopping.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- "One burden currency" sounds rigorous but is underdefined. Is the currency a dyadic flux budget, a localized enstrophy increment, a continuation criterion deficit, or something else? Those currencies do not convert cleanly. A route can look strong in the packet ledger and still be irrelevant in the physical-space theorem ledger.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:21:- The kill condition is too weak. The failure mode is not only "cannot be frozen in one currency." A more likely failure is worse: the chain can freeze everything neatly in one currency that later turns out to be the wrong currency for endpoint insertion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- "Declare what share of the full burden the promoted packet mechanism controls" is correct in spirit and dangerously soft in practice. Unless "share" is quantified against the full nonlinear burden near the target endpoint, the route can certify a mechanism that controls a visually interesting but theorem-irrelevant slice.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:49:### Step 4 - Reconstruct to the inherited endpoint and pay localization debt
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:57:- The phrase "map the packet gain back to one physical-space endpoint line on the LEI / CKN ledger" hides a severe mismatch of levels. A packet gain can be exact and still fail to correspond to any sharp improvement on the local continuation bottlenecks that matter for beyond-De Giorgi.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:58:- If the bad transfer pattern was frozen in a packet-native currency, the conversion to the inherited endpoint may itself cost more than the gain. The route acknowledges this possibility but understates how likely it is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:60:Failure mode: Step 4 shows that the only gains available are symbolic-Fourier gains that evaporate under summation, localization, and endpoint translation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:69:- Tao sensitivity is necessary but not sufficient. An artifact can use exact structure destroyed by averaging and still be useless for the Navier-Stokes endpoint. Distinctness from the averaged model is not the same as regularity leverage.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:79:- The failure taxonomy is too tidy. In reality this route is likely to fail for several reasons at once: prior-art overlap, mixed-helicity collapse, reconstruction loss, and endpoint mismatch. Forcing a single label can understate how overdetermined the failure is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:103:### 5. The endpoint mismatch is severe
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:105:The route starts in exact helical packet geometry and tries to finish on an LEI/CKN-style physical-space ledger. That is a major level mismatch. Unless the chain finds an unusually robust invariant that survives this translation, most symbolic gains will be spent before they reach the endpoint.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:122:The honest question is not whether exact helical packet structure exists. It does. The honest question is whether any packet-complete effect survives full mixed-helicity completion and then still has enough one-sided strength left after summation, localization, and endpoint insertion to matter for beyond-De Giorgi. That is a much harsher test, and this chain gives too many opportunities to confuse symbolic exactness with real leverage before that test is passed.
