## Progress-Currency And Threshold Ledger

- `[VERIFIED]` Frozen progress currency:
  quantified reduction of the specified nonlocal remainder, namely shrinkage of the effective coefficient on the same full far-field pairing `I_p^far`.
- `[VERIFIED]` Harmonic-moment cancellation is not a separate currency; it counts only if it is the mechanism producing that same coefficient shrinkage.
- `[PROPOSED]` Frozen minimum threshold:
  after later reconstruction and any required localization debt, the branch must still yield
  `|I_p^far| <= C_far,eff(k) 2^{12k/5} U_k^{6/5}`
  with
  `C_far,eff(k) <= (1-delta) ||u||_{L^2}^2 / r_k^3`
  for some uniform `delta > 0`, or an equivalent same-ledger full-pairing estimate with positive-margin net coefficient shrinkage.
- `[INFERRED]` Why this still counts as meaningful progress:
  it improves the already-frozen bad term in the same theorem ledger after later debt is repaid; it is not a prettier identity, a surrogate gain, or a change of architecture.
- `[VERIFIED]` Weaker thresholds are cosmetic and therefore rejected:
  constants are already annihilated by the pairing;
  affine-and-higher harmonic modes remain live;
  generic harmonic regularity is Tao-compatible unless it lowers the actual coefficient;
  and a gain on a local or representation-only subpiece that leaves the full-pairing coefficient unchanged does not count.

## Admission-Rules Note

- `[INFERRED]` Same-scale unconstrained exterior / harmonic rule:
  for the frozen endpoint
  `I_p^far = -∬ p_far div(v_k phi_k^2 e_hat)`,
  any later candidate that, after full harmonic accounting and any required localization debt, still leaves an uncontrolled same-scale affine-or-higher harmonic remainder in the full reconstructed pairing is an immediate branch failure, because no positive-margin coefficient shrinkage on the full pairing has been proved.
- `[INFERRED]` Tao rule:
  averaged-model sensitivity is mandatory but not sufficient; a candidate must fail the relevant averaged-model comparison, but that only counts if the same candidate also lowers the effective coefficient in the frozen full-pairing estimate for `I_p^far`.
- `[VERIFIED]` Both rules are tied to the frozen endpoint itself, not to free-floating pressure-Hessian rhetoric.

