# The Localized LEI Cutoff-Flux Bundle Is The Fixed Bad Term For The Audit

Status: `VERIFIED` term identification with `INFERRED` fixation

The fixed bad term for the Step-5 exact-rewrite audit is the localized LEI
cutoff-flux bundle

`I_flux[phi] = ∬_{Q_r} (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`.

This is the unique explicit location in the inherited local-energy inequality
where localized nonlinear transport and pressure transport are paid against the
same cutoff. It is therefore the correct target for comparing bounded exact
rewrites without changing architecture.

For this branch, the whole bundle stays fixed. A rewrite does not count as
progress if it only shifts cost between the cubic `|u|^2 u · ∇phi` piece and
the pressure-transport `p u · ∇phi` piece while leaving the same effective LEI
closure burden.

